# Project Architecture and Development Guide

## Technology Stack & Structure
- Next.js 15.4 with App Router
- TypeScript for type safety
- React 19 with functional components
- SCSS for styling
- Static export for GitHub Pages

## Key Directories
- `/app/` - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- `/src/components/` - React components by feature
- `/src/data/` - Static data files (resume, projects, stats)
- `/src/static/` - SCSS styles
- `/public/` - Static assets

## Development Commands
```bash
# Start dev server
npm run dev  # http://localhost:3000

# Build and check
npm run build  # Production build
npm run lint   # Run linting
npm test       # Run tests
```

## Important Development Rules
1. All pages must maintain original React site structure
2. Site uses static export (`output: 'export'`) for GitHub Pages
3. Client components must use 'use client' directive
4. Font optimization uses Next.js built-in optimization
5. TypeScript strict mode is enabled

## Data Management
- All site content is managed through TypeScript files in `/src/data/`
- Resume data: [src/data/resume/](mdc:src/data/resume/)
- Projects: [src/data/projects.ts](mdc:src/data/projects.ts)
- About info: [src/data/about.ts](mdc:src/data/about.ts)
- Contact: [src/data/contact.ts](mdc:src/data/contact.ts)

## Styling Guidelines
- Use SCSS modules with shared variables
- Main styles in [src/static/css/main.scss](mdc:src/static/css/main.scss)
- Follow existing component style structure